The paper deals with graph embeddings and minors for directed graphs, which are topics that are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the usefulness of these operations in characterizing certain classes of graphs, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph algorithms (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents a generalization of earlier results on series-parallel graphs, which is a topic that is relevant to the study of large-scale networks and complex systems (cs.LG).
